FB.ATM.TOTL.P5-access.def: Automated teller machines are computerized telecommunications devices that provide clients of a financial institution with access to financial transactions in a public place.
FB.ATM.TOTL.P5-access.name: Automated teller machines
FB.ATM.TOTL.P5-access.source: International Monetary Fund, Financial Access Survey.

FB.CBK.BRCH.P5-access.def: Commercial bank branches are retail locations of resident commercial banks and other resident banks that function as commercial banks that provide financial services to customers and are physically separated from the main office but not organized as legally separated subsidiaries.
FB.CBK.BRCH.P5-access.name: Commercial bank branches
FB.CBK.BRCH.P5-access.source: International Monetary Fund, Financial Access Survey.

FB.CBK.BRWR.P3-access.def: Borrowers from commercial banks are the reported number of resident customers that are nonfinancial corporations (public and private) and households who obtained loans from commercial banks and other banks functioning as commercial banks. For many countries data cover the total number of loan accounts due to lack of information on loan account holders.
FB.CBK.BRWR.P3-access.name: Borrowers from commercial banks
FB.CBK.BRWR.P3-access.source: International Monetary Fund, Financial Access Survey.

FB.CBK.DPTR.P3-access.def: Depositors with commercial banks are the reported number of deposit account holders at commercial banks and other resident banks functioning as commercial banks that are resident nonfinancial corporations (public and private) and households. For many countries data cover the total number of deposit accounts due to lack of information on account holders. The major types of deposits are checking accounts, savings accounts, and time deposits.
FB.CBK.DPTR.P3-access.name: Depositors with commercial banks
FB.CBK.DPTR.P3-access.source: International Monetary Fund, Financial Access Survey.

FX.OWN.TOTL.40.ZS-access.def: Account denotes the percentage of respondents who report having an account (by themselves or together with someone else) at a bank or another type of financial institution or report personally using a mobile money service in the past 12 months (poorest 40%, share of population ages 15+).
FX.OWN.TOTL.40.ZS-access.name: Account ownership at a financial institution or with a mobile-money-service provider
FX.OWN.TOTL.40.ZS-access.source: Demirguc-Kunt et al., 2018, Global Financial Inclusion Database, World Bank.

SI.RMT.COST.IB.ZS-access.def: Average transaction cost of sending remittance to a specific country is the average of the total transaction cost in percentage of the amount sent for sending USD 200 charged by each single remittance service provider (RSP) included in the Remittance Prices Worldwide (RPW) database to a specific country.
SI.RMT.COST.IB.ZS-access.name: Average transaction cost of sending remittances to a specific country
SI.RMT.COST.IB.ZS-access.source: World Bank, Remittance Prices Worldwide, available at http://remittanceprices.worldbank.org

SI.RMT.COST.OB.ZS-access.def: Average transaction cost of sending remittance from a specific country is the average of the total transaction cost in percentage of the amount sent for sending USD 200 charged by each single remittance service provider (RSP) included in the Remittance Prices Worldwide (RPW) database from a specific country.
SI.RMT.COST.OB.ZS-access.name: Average transaction cost of sending remittances from a specific country
SI.RMT.COST.OB.ZS-access.source: World Bank, Remittance Prices Worldwide, available at http://remittanceprices.worldbank.org
